commit.message: pk: add long help for `pk dep compare` and `pk cpv compare`
pk version compare: add initial comparison expression long help with example
pk: improve descriptions for `cpv`, `dep`, and `version` subcommands
cargo: update transitive deps
cargo: update dep versions
cargo: update dep versions and port to the latest nix release

restrict command line tool clap struct/enum visibility

To fix unreachable_pub lint warnings.
pkgcruft: export benchmark modules to avoid unreachable_pub lints
cargo: use workspace lints supported in rust-1.74
ci: drop lcov artifacts after 3 days
cargo: update dep versions and bump MSRV to 1.74 for the latest clap
pkgcraft: drop unnecessary path from Cargo.toml

pkgcruft: use lazily generated mappings for check selection options

Instead of iterating over all available checks for each value.
pkgcruft: add ordered maps for source->checks and report->checks
pkgcruft show reports: add basic -l/--levels tests

pkgcruft show reports: drop -c/--color option and default to using colors

Colors should be automatically disabled in unsupported environments or
when not run in an interactive terminal. NO_COLOR usage (as described at
https://no-color.org/) should also work as expected.
pkgcruft show reports: add -l/--levels option support
pkgcruft show reports: add -c/--color option support
cargo: update dep versions
readme: use named reference links instead of numbers

pkgcraft: replace non-test global usage with `test` feature query

So test module support isn't needed for release builds.
ci: drop unnecessary newline for pkgcruft release workflow

ci: don't enable all features for pkgcruft release builds

Currently this means disabling test support that is unnecessary for
releases.
